Below is a structured extraction of the **Emergency Credit Line Guarantee Scheme (ECLGS 5.0)** as presented on the JanSamarth portal, along with relevant details from the official implementation guidelines and FAQs.

---

# Emergency Credit Line Guarantee Scheme (ECLGS 5.0)

**Official Portal:** [JanSamarth ECLGS 5.0 Page](https://www.jansamarth.in/emergency-credit-line-guarantee-scheme?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

## Overview

| Field              | Value                                                                               |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Scheme Name        | Emergency Credit Line Guarantee Scheme (ECLGS) 5.0                                  |
| Administered By    | National Credit Guarantee Trustee Company Limited                                   |
| Application Portal | [JanSamarth Portal](https://www.jansamarth.in/home?utm_source=chatgpt.com)          |
| Type               | Credit Guarantee Scheme                                                             |
| Benefit Type       | Additional Working Capital Loan                                                     |
| Primary Objective  | Provide emergency liquidity support to businesses affected by the West Asia crisis  |
| Valid Till         | 31 March 2027 (or till guarantee limit is exhausted) ([Prime Minister of India][1]) |

---

# Objective

The scheme provides **government-backed guarantee coverage** to banks so that they can extend **additional working capital** to eligible businesses without increasing lending risk.

The intention is to:

* maintain business continuity
* prevent liquidity shortages
* protect employment
* maintain supply chains
* support MSMEs and other businesses facing temporary financial stress due to external disruptions. ([Prime Minister of India][1])

---

# Primary Benefits

## 1. Additional Working Capital

Eligible borrowers receive an additional Working Capital Term Loan.

---

## 2. No Additional Collateral

No fresh collateral security is required.

Existing securities continue to secure both the existing loan and ECLGS loan.

---

## 3. Zero Fees

* Processing Fee: NIL
* Guarantee Fee: NIL
* Prepayment Penalty: NIL

([Bank of Maharashtra][2])

---

## 4. Government Guarantee

Government guarantee coverage:

| Borrower       | Guarantee |
| -------------- | --------- |
| MSMEs          | 100%      |
| Non-MSMEs      | 90%       |
| Airline Sector | 90%       |

([Prime Minister of India][1])

---

# Who Can Apply?

Eligible borrowers include:

* MSMEs
* Non-MSME business enterprises
* Scheduled passenger airlines (special provisions)

provided they already have eligible working capital facilities. ([Prime Minister of India][1])

---

# Eligibility Criteria

A borrower must satisfy all of the following.

## Existing Working Capital

Must already have fund-based working capital facilities.

---

## Account Status

Loan account must be:

* Standard Account
* Not classified as SMA-2

as on **31 March 2026**.

---

## NPA Status

Borrower must **not** become NPA before sanction/disbursement.

---

## Existing Borrower

Applicable only to existing borrowers.

---

## Export Scheme Condition

Borrowers who have already availed facilities under the Credit Guarantee Scheme for Exporters (CGSE) receive eligibility only after adjusting the limit already availed.

([Canara Bank][3])

---

# Ineligible Borrowers / Sectors

The JanSamarth page lists several excluded sectors.

These include:

* NBFCs
* Power
* Telecom
* Sugar
* Ethanol
* Information Technology
* Paper & Paper Products
* Educational Institutions
* Beverage industry (except Tea/Coffee)
* Tobacco

([HDBFS][4])

---

# Loan Amount

## General Businesses

Maximum:

**20% of peak working capital outstanding**

during

**1 January 2026 – 31 March 2026**

subject to:

Maximum ₹100 crore per borrower.

---

## Airline Sector

Eligible up to

100% of outstanding credit

subject to applicable cap and conditions.

([Prime Minister of India][1])

---

# Loan Tenure

## MSME & Non-MSME

* Total tenure: 5 years
* Principal moratorium: 1 year

---

## Airlines

* Total tenure: 7 years
* Principal moratorium: 2 years

([Prime Minister of India][1])

---

# Interest Rate

Interest is determined by participating lenders.

Typical cap:

Around **9% p.a.** depending on borrower category and lender.

([BOI][5])

---

# Security

Existing:

* Primary security
* Collateral security

continue.

No additional collateral is required.

Charge is created over:

* existing securities
* assets financed under ECLGS

([Bank of Maharashtra][2])

---

# Application Process

1. Visit the JanSamarth Portal.
2. Select ECLGS.
3. Check eligibility.
4. Authenticate using required details.
5. Submit application digitally.
6. Lending institution evaluates.
7. Loan sanctioned.
8. Funds disbursed.

Applications must be routed through JanSamarth. ([Canara Bank][3])

---

# Documents Required

The JanSamarth FAQ indicates that documentation varies by scheme, but applicants should generally be ready with:

* Aadhaar
* PAN
* Bank account details
* Identity proof
* Business information
* Existing loan information
* Any additional lender-specific documents

([JanSamarth][6])

---

# Important Conditions

* Existing borrower only
* Standard account mandatory
* No SMA-2
* No NPA
* Working capital facility must already exist
* Government guarantee available only through participating lenders
* Scheme valid until 31 March 2027 or exhaustion of guarantee corpus

([Prime Minister of India][1])

---

# Frequently Asked Questions

### What is the purpose of ECLGS?

To provide emergency working capital support to businesses facing temporary liquidity stress. ([Prime Minister of India][1])

---

### Is collateral required?

No.

Fresh collateral is not required.

---

### Is there any processing fee?

No.

Processing fee is NIL.

---

### Is there any guarantee fee?

No.

Guarantee fee is NIL.

---

### Can I prepay without penalty?

Yes.

No prepayment penalty.

---

### How much loan can I receive?

Generally:

Up to **20% of peak working capital outstanding** during Q4 FY 2025–26, subject to the prescribed cap. Airlines have separate limits. ([Prime Minister of India][1])

---

### Who provides the guarantee?

National Credit Guarantee Trustee Company Limited provides the guarantee to participating lenders. ([Prime Minister of India][1])

---

### Until when is the scheme available?

Up to **31 March 2027**, or until the approved guarantee amount is exhausted. ([Prime Minister of India][1])

---

